<bug>
    <id>2067</id>
    <title>/dev/stdin: Stale NFS file handle0.9.0</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">Steps to reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.2">1 Run the base Ubuntu image `docker run -i -t ubuntu /bin/bash`</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.3">2 Install the package `openssh-client` to get `ssh-keygen`: `apt-get install openssh-client`</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.4">3 `ssh-keygen -lf /dev/stdin &lt;&lt;&lt; 'ssh-rsa  root@f1d7fcdadc01'`</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">Following the symlinks, `/dev/stdin` → `/dev/fd/0` → `/dev/pts/4`, it seems like the last link is broken.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">The only thing existing in `/dev/pts/` is `ptmx`.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">It is not possible to pipe stuff to `ssh-keygen`, so I *think* I am dependent on `/dev/stdin` working as on my host system.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Any ideas?</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">Is this a bug?</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
